column5: Hello People, launched at Trenton on Monday morning, it was a bit breezy, boat control was an issue. The fishing was slow but we managed a few. The bass were tight in cover. Nothing to brag about (the bass that is), however I did get a PB freshwater drum, what a mutant.               One last fish after a beautiful day on Quinte          Cheers....
Looks like a fun time. Nice sheepshead
That Sheephead looks more like a bronzeback in the first picture! LOL
What a monster.  My pb sheepy came from very close to there as well.  I bet it fought a little harder than those little green thingys
That's a big sheepy.  That sign on the bridge is kinda cool.  Thanks for the report!
Cool report and like the others have said good on you for the PB sheepshead! Nice going. Not a bad tee shirt and hat too wink.  Pidge.
